
[1]ceylanite

   CEYLANITE, n. A mineral, classed with the ruby family; called also
   pleonaste. Its color is a muddy, dark blue, and grayish black,
   approaching to iron black. It occurs in grains, or small crystals,
   either perfect octahedrons, or truncated on the edges, or with the
   angles acuminated by four planes. It occurs also in rhomboidal
   dodecahedrons.
